# Public open-release allowlist. Default-private at the TOP LEVEL: a tracked file
# is published only if it sits under one of these entries (so a new top-level dir
# is private until explicitly added here — the leak-safe default). Private
# OVERRIDES inside an allowlisted tree (notably src/pro/) are stripped by
# scripts/publish_open.sh regardless. gitignored paths (docs/, CLAUDE.md, build/)
# are already excluded because the export draws from `git ls-files`.
src
include
tests
tools
scripts
third_party
CMakeLists.txt
LICENSE
NOTICE
README.md
.gitmodules
.gitignore
